      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "197919e71f81de6f",
      "text": "When asked about the meaning of the base and their scrambler, they will often give simple definitions that they looked up. When asked how these might connect to their interests, they will struggle either to define a connection or even to name an interest. Here is where [[Deep Listening]] is essential. Be curious about them, help them to name an interest and challenge them to find a connection. And then allow them a moment of silence to turn that struggle into a creative 'grapple'. As they give a response, encourage them to go deeper. Then quickly move on to the next student."
